Midgaard's Guard Command recognizes Crusader Corps credentials under the same framework as Knight
and Swordsman academy credentials, with an additional field-service notation acknowledging synthesis.
Guard Command officer corps includes Crusader-trained officers in positions requiring combined
offensive and defensive capability. Reserve depot cross-training programs are now formally documented
in Guard Command's training charter. The Anti Magic Shell's usefulness in urban civil unrest contexts—
where magical disruption by unlicensed practitioners is a recurring problem—has made Crusader
practitioners specifically valued in internal security assignments.

