---
Kiess's Roc Road escort function is the most demanding active operational environment for Crusader
practitioners in the five-city network. The frontier context provides actual tactical engagements
against route predators—where Knight formation discipline and Swordsman individual excellence are
tested against opponents who have adapted to both in isolation. Wall Command rates Crusader capability
above either parent tradition for convoy escort in contested terrain: formation discipline for ambush
response, individual escalating momentum for close-quarters pursuit. The Anti Magic Shell is valued
in Roc Road contexts because eastern frontier route predators increasingly employ magical disruption
as a first-contact technique.

flags RAKUEN
---
Rakuen's Ember Warden doctrine places highest value on versatility in resource-constrained conditions.
Crusader practitioners, whose synthesis training explicitly targets adaptability across formation and
individual contexts, align with this requirement. The Canopy Compact's collective accountability
framework fits with the Crusader Corps' founding principle that doctrine governs institutional loyalty.
Rakuen has limited access to dedicated Knight academies or Swordsman dueling courts; Crusader
practitioners who completed both paths elsewhere are valued as instructors transmitting both traditions
where full institutional access to either is unavailable.

