Khephari cyclical-durability doctrine—what endures does so through structural soundness tested
repeatedly over time rather than peak performance under ideal conditions—maps naturally onto the
Crusader Corps' founding insight. The Solar Court's original campaign-honor recognized practitioners
who remained structurally sound through continuous successive engagements; the Crusader Corps
synthesis produces practitioners more structurally sound under varied conditions than single-tradition
practitioners. Khephari practitioners entering the Crusader tradition through Kiess's Roc Road
operational environment find the tradition's combination of defensive resilience and sustained
momentum aligns with their cultural framework for endurance through structural testing.
